snippet.textDisplay:
Hi, English Brit here!!

I just want to firstly say how sorry I am that one of your fellow American women has been treated so appallingly by our press, it's just not acceptable. There is a very sour taste in the air over here, mainly created by very old fashioned and ignorant people - believe me though, a lot of us are well and truly backing them in their decision but unfortunately it's always the crap that gets noticed. I think there are people that consider themselves "royalists" over here but are in fact just nasty backward thinking people with no brain cells. Harry quite clearly is still suffering with the events surrounding his mothers death and the way he, William and his mother were hounded by the press - it is understandable that he wants to escape this and take his family to a safer, purer, environment. I think the issue some people have with Meghan is she was something different and wasn't prepared enough for Royal life. It's not something you can adjust to overnight. Do I think they married too quickly? Yes, I do. I think they should have considered the fact our press can be nasty, our press are invasive - because they are. However if it felt right for them, then that's their decision. Is it because Meghan is a black woman? Partly. I know this may be hard to believe considering the racism in states, but over here it's not really a "black & white" thing like in the USA, it's more a xenophobic "white & muslim" thing - which obviously is still absolutely abhorrent and there is no excuse for racism or xenophobia. Yes, some people are bothered by the fact she is mixed race, but it's a VERY minor percentage, it's primarily down to the way she's conducted herself (which has at times gone against protocol) and the fact she's obviously made Harry a more independent man and the "royalists" can't stand that. The press have indeed tried to make it a racial issue but are failing because it honestly doesn't come down to her race, it's more her personality, her "motives" as some are ridiculously presuming. There are people that don't like the fact she's a very ordinary woman from a very ordinary background from a different country, that's managed to capture the heart of the beloved Prince.
